<!-- Use Case 4: Climate Survey -->
                <div class="project-card">
                    <div class="project-header">
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="project-title">Large-Scale Climate & Engagement Assessment</h3>
                        </div>
                        <div class="project-badge">Stakeholder Engagement</div>
                    </div>
                    <p class="project-description">
                        <strong>The Challenge:</strong> Organizations need to know what tens of thousands of stakeholders really think‚Äîbut survey fatigue is real, and most feedback systems generate reports that sit on shelves. The challenge is designing assessment processes that people actually complete and that produce insights leadership can immediately act on.
                    </p>
                    <div class="project-highlights">
                        <h5>How Qualtrics Enables This:</h5>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Sophisticated survey designs with smart branching that feel personalized rather than generic</li>
                            <li>Role-based dashboards delivering the right insights to the right people at the right level</li>
                            <li>Sentiment analysis and trend modeling that surface patterns hidden in thousands of responses</li>
                            <li>Automated systems tracking metrics over time to show whether improvements stick</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="project-impact">
                        <div class="impact-metric">
                            <span class="impact-icon">üéØ</span>
                            <span><strong>What Success Looks Like:</strong> High response rates from diverse groups, leadership making course corrections based on real feedback, measurable satisfaction improvements, and assessment becoming part of continuous improvement rather than compliance theater.</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

<!-- Use Case 5: Strategic Planning -->
                <div class="project-card">
                    <div class="project-header">
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="project-title">Strategic Planning & Organizational Transformation</h3>
                        </div>
                        <div class="project-badge">Organizational Change</div>
                    </div>
                    <p class="project-description">
                        <strong>The Challenge:</strong> Strategic plans often die in binders because they're created at the top and rolled out to skeptical staff. Real transformation requires bringing everyone into the process, making data transparent, and building organizational capacity to act on what you learn‚Äînot just writing better goals.
                    </p>
                    <div class="project-highlights">
                        <h5>How Qualtrics Enables This:</h5>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Broad stakeholder input systems that make diverse voices visible in strategic decisions</li>
                            <li>Visualization tools showing how community feedback actually shapes organizational priorities</li>
                            <li>Performance tracking systems connecting goals to implementation and accountability</li>
                            <li>Continuous feedback mechanisms maintaining momentum through multi-year change efforts</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="project-impact">
                        <div class="impact-metric">
                            <span class="impact-icon">üéØ</span>
                            <span><strong>What Success Looks Like:</strong> Strategic plans with genuine buy-in, boards and communities aligned around shared priorities, culture shifts that outlast superintendents, and organizations that actually use data instead of just collecting it.</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
<!-- Use Case: VA Employee Experience & Retention -->
                <div class="project-card">
                    <div class="project-header">
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="project-title">VA Employee Experience & Retention Strategy</h3>
                        </div>
                        <div class="project-badge">Veterans Affairs</div>
                    </div>
                    <p class="project-description">
                        <strong>The Challenge:</strong> VA organizations face brutal turnover rates‚Äîoften 40% in clinical roles‚Äîwhile serving a dual mission: taking care of employees AND the veterans who depend on them. Generic engagement surveys miss what actually drives retention in military-aligned cultures. The challenge is diagnosing what matters most and giving frontline supervisors the insights to act before good people leave.
                    </p>
                    <div class="project-highlights">
                        <h5>How Qualtrics Enables This:</h5>
                        <ul>
                            <li>EX25 framework benchmarking VA organizations against government sector norms, not corporate standards</li>
                            <li>Predictive analytics identifying which drivers actually predict retention in VA contexts (work-life balance, mission connection, supervisor trust)</li>
                            <li>Manager-level dashboards with action-ready insights‚Äînot just numbers but "here's what to do about it"</li>
                            <li>Lifecycle measurement capturing onboarding, pulse checks, and exit insights to pinpoint exactly when and why people leave</li>
                            <li>Veteran satisfaction linkage showing how employee experience directly impacts quality of care metrics</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="project-impact">
                        <div class="impact-metric">
                            <span class="impact-icon">üéØ</span>
                            <span><strong>What Success Looks Like:</strong> Turnover reduction of 10-20% saving $150K-$300K annually, CMS quality ratings improving alongside staff engagement, managers equipped with data to retain top performers, and veteran satisfaction scores rising because happy staff deliver better care.</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>      

<!-- Use Case: Government Sentiment Intelligence -->
<div class="project-card">
